        "subtitle": "Shou Sugi Ban Damascus — The Stunner",
        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>Xinzuo Mo Series (X06)</strong> is “The Stunner” — where serious cutting performance meets striking visual design. Each blade features <strong>67-layer Damascus steel</strong> with a 10Cr15CoMoV core at HRC 60, delivering the same edge retention as higher-priced Damascus series. What sets the Mo apart is its handle: burnt oak crafted using the Japanese <strong>Shou Sugi Ban</strong> charring technique, creating a distinctive dark finish that is both beautiful and naturally resistant to moisture. The range includes chef knives, santoku, nakiri, bunka, and specialty blades like the Viking knife and bone chopper. For cooks who want Damascus performance with a blade that looks as good as it cuts, the Mo Series is the standout choice.</p>",
